Package iwork.eheap2

Interface Summary
EventCallback An interface that contains a single method that accepts an array of events and returns an integer indicating whether further callbacks are desired.
EventHeapConfigValues This is an interface that contains members with the default settings for the Event Heap
EventRegistration A class with this interface is returned by EventHeap.registerForEvents(Event[], EventCallback) as a handle to allow deregistering for the specified events.
FieldValueTypes This is an interface that contains members with the enumerations for valid value types for the post and template value sub-fields of event fields.
 

Class Summary
ACLManager ACLManager is a utility class designed to aid application developers manage the handling of an application's access control lists.
Event This class represents events either retrieved from or to be placed into an Event Heap using the EventHeap class.
EventHeap This class provides an interface to an event heap in which the application is participating.
Field This class represents a field in an Event.
FieldType Encodes the type for a field as both an Event Heap standard type string and the equivalent Java class if it exists.
FieldValue This class represents a value for either the postValue or templateValue sub-field of a Field object.
SecureEvent This class represents secure events either retrieved from or to be placed into a Secure Event Heap using the SecureEventHeap class.
SecureEventHeap This class provides an interface to an event heap in which the application is participating.
Tuple A Tuple is the super-class of Event.
WrappedObject This class represents an object of a type that may not be accessible to the JVM under which this java application is running.
 

Exception Summary
EventHeapException This is the exception class for the Event Heap.
